                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15230.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State ad interim</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-16T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1915—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>645. Your 777, June 15, 3 p.m., and 779, June 15, 6 p.m. I have just complied
                    with both requests. Cooperation of principal colleagues already in active work
                    and I think all the others will help. They think peaceful settlement greatly
                    depends upon calm discussion between factions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
